      <div class="step screensteps-section screensteps-depth-1" id="change_self_registration" data-step-uuid="6357382f-d708-4761-bc25-0fc6e642e749">
    <h2 id="change_self_registration" class="step-title screensteps-heading">Configure Self Registration</h2>
        <div class="image screensteps-image">
      <img src="https://media.screensteps.com/image_assets/assets/005/527/832/original/e1e21390-b280-4d15-99f7-1ba7fbfae3c8.png" srcset="" alt="Configure Self Registration" height="507" width="698">
  </div>
 
      <div class="step-instructions screensteps-textblock">
  <div id="text-content_16AFB0F0-1CAB-0135-C98C-22000B5A851D" class="text-block-content">
    <p>By default, Self Registration is disabled. To enable Self Registration, select the radio button for the registration type for your account. </p>
<p>To allow self registration for all users, select the <strong>All Account Types</strong> option [1]. To limit self registration to observers (including parents), select the <strong>Observer Accounts Only</strong> option [2].</p>
<p>To require users to complete a Captcha form before completing the registation process, click the <strong>Require Captcha for Self Registration</strong> checkbox [3].</p>
<p>Canvas enforces MFA is functionally equivalent to the legacy UIs checkbox for MFA Required being enabled. </p>
<p>To have Canvas enforce the MFA, select the <strong>Canvas enforces MFA </strong>option [4].  </p>
<p>To have the user opt in, select <strong>User can opt in to MFA </strong>option [5].</p>
<p><strong>Note:</strong> If the All Account Types option is selected, it is recommended to require users to complete a Captcha form to avoid the creation of spam users.</p>
  </div>
</div>
 
  </div>

      <div class="step screensteps-section screensteps-depth-1" id="save_self_registration" data-step-uuid="1a9225cc-e876-47fd-be20-cf7bee6b50aa">
